<dl id="n40078a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40078a">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40078a"> 78(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Abacides</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&hellip; these sectarians <font color="green">[Islamic separatists who disputed that the Ommiades were the legitimate successors of Mohammed]</font>, favoured by the learned, and by the Abbasides in their jealous hatred of the Ommiades, went to the extreme length of the Ali-Il&aacute;hi &mdash; the God-makers of Ali. <small> Richard F. Burton, &ldquo;Terminal Essay&rdquo;, <a name="RBTE2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#RBTE2"><cite title="source">The Book of the Thousand Nights and a Night</cite></a> (n.d.) X, 191</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
